{{Quote|There are communications transceivers set into the wall every couple of yards, so you can communicate naturally with the swimmers on the other side of the barrier.|[[Mone]]|<ref name="SW74">[[Star Wars (1977) 74|''Star Wars'' (1977) 74]]</ref>}}
A '''communications transceiver''',<ref name="SW74" /> or '''communication transceiver''', was a device that allowed communications to be carried out across long distances<ref name="DB">{{DB|starship|droidtrifighter|droid tri-fighter}}</ref> or through physical barriers such as walls or bodies of [[Water/Legends|water]].<ref name="SW74" />

==Details and uses==
The [[Droid tri-fighter/Legends|droid tri-fighters]] of the [[Confederate Navy/Legends|Confederate Navy]] were equipped with advanced communication transceivers, which, along with the [[Starship/Legends|craft's]] robust [[Power plant/Legends|power plant]], afforded it an impressive operating range for an automated [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] not equipped with a [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]].<ref name="DB" />

The interior walls in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Pavillion]] on [[Iskalon/Legends|Iskalon]] were fitted with communications transceivers, spaced at regular intervals of a few yards, which allowed communications between [[Iskalonian]]s in the waters outside and "air-breathers" who remained in the self-contained underwater city. [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] was able to speak with [[Primor (Inleshat)|Primor]] in this manner during his visit to Pavillion.<ref name="SW74" />

[[Escape pod/Legends|Escape pods]] were equipped with limited communications transceivers that scanned for any activity on standard frequencies.<ref name="EGVV">''[[The Essential Guide to Vehicles and Vessels]]''</ref>

[[Cybernetics/Legends|Cybernetic]] units such as [[BioTech Industries/Legends|BioTech Industries']] [[AJ^6 cyborg construct/Legends|AJ^6 cyborg construct]] had communications transceivers embedded into the headband.<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

